  "title": "Thermal energy transfer - two materials",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> is placed in thermal contact with Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>. Initially, Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> has a greater temperature than Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following statements best predicts the energy transfer as a result of collisions between atoms of Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> and atoms of Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is more likely that energy will transfer from Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> atoms to Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> atoms.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is more likely that energy will transfer from Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> atoms to Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> atoms.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is equally likely that energy will transfer from Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> atoms to Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> atoms.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">No energy will transfer between Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> atoms and Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> atoms.</p>",
